A BILL FOR AN ACT
RELATING TO COMMUNITY BEHAVIORAL HEALTH CLINICS.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF HAWAII:
1 SECTION 1. The Hawaii Revised Statutes is amended by
2 adding a new chapter to title 19 to be appropriately designated
3 and to read as follows:
4 "CHAPTER
5 CERTIFIED COMMUNITY BEHAVIORAL HEALTH CLINICS
6 § -1 Purpose. The purpose of this chapter is to
7 establish a community behavioral health clinics certifying
8 office to certify community behavioral health clinics and
9 provide technical assistance for clinics seeking certification
10 under federal guidelines to promote consistency and
11 accessibility for all people of the State to mental health and
12 substance use services.
13 § -2 Definitions. As used in this chapter, unless the
14 context otherwise requires:
15 "Board" means the certified community behavioral health
16 clinics oversight board.
